content: How to rate this? Wow. I thought this would be an easy and quick app. Not so. Paid the $9.00. Trying to navigate and learn this is not worth the money, especially since my bank statement says it is a recurring charge. There are simpler apps that can do what I want at no cost. $9.00 recurring charges is definitely not worth the hassle of this app. Tried it because of other people on sites I use. Definitely going to unintall and call to stop any future charges.
replyContent: Hi Ronnie, regarding there being a recurring charge: PinPal is (and has always been) a one-time purchase. There is no recurring charge. The purchase is tied to the Google account you buy it with, and you can download it for free once you've purchased. Feel free to reach out to us at PinPalAndroid@gmail.com for further assistance.

I'm providing an update as I wrote the above "review" 4 months ago and had sent Jeff an email voicing my frustration with the app. I've received NO response from him in that time and have sent him yet another email (see below). If not, why not?  As I mentioned to you in a previous email and a review post, the inability to obtain NIGHTLY stats is a HUGE issue. This is a ideal app for tracking scoring frame by frame. Easy to record each frame so you can concentrate on bowling on not score keeping. Nice stats and charts features, now I know how many @$#@ 10-pins I miss.  The new 'Share' feature is really nice.  This feature allows the bowler to share games and series data either by text or by image (jpeg) to most any third party platform, IE messaging, e-mail, facebook, google+, etc.  The image share feature allows the bowler to filter the title, date, and bowling alley on the image, really nice.  Also, there is a new sweet Tournament section!  The only downside to the app is the lack of a direct export routine.  Howerver, the 'share' feature can be used to get an export. You can send the scores to your e-mail account, then copy the scores from the e-mail to a spreadsheet.  Kind of the long way around by it works.  This is a nice app, well thought out; I would recommend it to any bowler.
